Based on this report, we managed to fit the patterns with a derived commensurate Imma model, reaching a satisfactory result. A careful inspection of the patterns showed no evidence of an incommensurate structure. Indeed, no additional peaks of a modulated phase are observed in our data set. Thus, we concluded that our perovskite, according to NPD data, exhibits a low-temperature phase (2–148.3 K) defined in a Pnma orthorhombic symmetry, a novel orthorhombic Imma phase (148.8–153.8 K), a tetragonal structure defined in the I4/mcm space group (154.5–228.5 K) and a high-temperature phase (233.1–300 K) in a cubic Pm3¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
